WEBVTT

00:14.040 --> 00:15.520
Can I have a decaf, please?

00:21.640 --> 00:23.760
"Hello, this is
Mariví's answering machine.

00:23.840 --> 00:26.160
When you hear the beep,
you can leave a message."

00:27.080 --> 00:29.040
Mum, I've just finished. It's...

00:34.240 --> 00:36.640
Excuse me, do you have a phone charger?

00:36.920 --> 00:37.920
No.

00:43.320 --> 00:44.520
Do you want to use mine?

00:46.920 --> 00:49.600
20 HOURS INTO THE ROBBERY

00:51.920 --> 00:54.200
-Really? Don't you mind?
-No, no.

00:54.280 --> 00:56.240
Are you sure? Thanks.

00:57.600 --> 00:59.240
I have to make a couple of calls.

01:00.000 --> 01:01.680
-It's all right.
-Thanks a lot.

01:04.840 --> 01:07.200
SATURDAY 6:25 AM

01:10.640 --> 01:12.720
Mum, I've just finished, I'm on my way.

01:16.960 --> 01:19.240
"Superintendent Sánchez,
leave your message."

01:20.440 --> 01:23.280
This is inspector Murillo.
I know it's late,

01:23.360 --> 01:26.480
but I wanted to tell that,
if Intelligence is in charge,

01:26.560 --> 01:29.080
due to I don't know
which type of diplomatic interests,

01:29.640 --> 01:33.560
I'm not going to be your figurehead
while those thugs force their way there.

01:34.320 --> 01:35.840
So I feel obliged...

01:36.320 --> 01:38.920
to resign. Good night.

01:40.200 --> 01:41.240
Good morning.

01:45.200 --> 01:47.040
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

01:58.320 --> 02:01.200
Excuse me, but you're...

02:03.120 --> 02:04.400
It's you...

02:04.840 --> 02:07.280
"I started telling
the story of a kidnapping,

02:07.440 --> 02:09.760
because everybody will remember
those days of siege

02:09.840 --> 02:11.640
in the Fábrica Nacional
de Moneda y Timbre.

02:11.720 --> 02:15.640
The streets downtown were closed, all TV
channels broadcasted live for 24 hours,

02:15.720 --> 02:17.840
the police burnt their academy manuals

02:17.920 --> 02:20.200
and they didn't know
how to eat that pie in the sky

02:20.280 --> 02:23.360
of those poor wretches trying to print
their own money,

02:23.760 --> 02:26.680
but many other things happened
and nobody remembers them,

02:26.760 --> 02:28.120
things that changed us all

02:28.280 --> 02:30.880
to the point of not knowing
who the bad guys were...

02:31.280 --> 02:32.400
and who the good guys were."

02:32.680 --> 02:34.720
Excuse me,
when you negotiate with those people,

02:34.800 --> 02:37.200
do you give them what they want
or do you just have a chinwag

02:37.280 --> 02:38.560
to buy some time or...?

02:40.040 --> 02:42.640
-Well, don't answer me, I just...
-Every case is different.

02:43.240 --> 02:44.320
Sure, I'm sorry.

02:45.640 --> 02:46.560
But...

02:47.960 --> 02:48.920
But well, yes,

02:49.880 --> 02:52.760
we try to calm things down
and buy some time.

02:53.800 --> 02:54.680
Thanks.

02:55.000 --> 02:57.200
"In fact, we were the ones buying time,

02:57.280 --> 03:00.080
the sentence time is money
had never been better used.

03:00.720 --> 03:02.200
A lot of money.

03:02.760 --> 03:04.960
Every hour we printed eight million euros,

03:05.640 --> 03:08.280
1,400 sheets of paper money
from which we cut

03:08.360 --> 03:10.840
140,000 50 euro notes.

03:18.760 --> 03:21.320
Everything was so calm
during the hours of dawn

03:21.400 --> 03:23.280
that it seemed the plan
was going smoothly.

03:25.840 --> 03:27.760
The Professor was our Big Brother.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.520
He controlled the police radio
and 18 cameras,

03:31.560 --> 03:33.520
so if somebody wanted to fuck us,

03:33.960 --> 03:36.120
we'd know it well in advance.

03:41.080 --> 03:45.400
We took turns to watch the hostages,
the entries and of course the production.

03:45.880 --> 03:47.400
After only 20 hours there

03:47.480 --> 03:50.520
the presses had already spit
52 million euros,

03:51.080 --> 03:53.600
so at that point
we all thought it was possible.

03:54.600 --> 03:58.040
But all that calm
was just the calm before the storm.

03:58.120 --> 04:02.360
Things were going to screw up so much, we
would be on the brink of losing the game.

04:03.360 --> 04:04.720
And if you ask me why,

04:05.360 --> 04:07.520
I'll say it's due to a simple love story.

04:08.120 --> 04:11.320
After all, love is a good reason
to make everything go wrong."

05:36.600 --> 05:37.920
I'd like to ask you a favour.

05:40.600 --> 05:41.520
May I?

05:44.320 --> 05:46.440
"There's movement,
everyone get ready."

05:47.280 --> 05:49.360
Deputy inspector,
they're opening the doors.

05:55.680 --> 05:58.160
"There are seven men,
armed with M-16s, sir."

05:58.320 --> 06:00.000
Don't do anything, all right?

06:00.720 --> 06:03.800
-It's a unique opportunity.
-Don't do anything.

06:03.880 --> 06:05.200
Take off your mask.

06:14.920 --> 06:16.720
I'm begging you, please, not to shoot.

06:18.400 --> 06:19.960
My name's Mónica Gaztambide.

06:20.640 --> 06:21.640
She's a hostage.

06:22.520 --> 06:24.280
I'm just here to read a statement.

06:25.480 --> 06:28.640
I'm speaking on behalf of the robbers.

06:29.840 --> 06:32.080
We're 67 hostages,

06:32.680 --> 06:37.400
all of us in perfect health
and well cared of.

06:38.640 --> 06:41.760
There are no victims or wounded.
We're all dressed alike

06:42.600 --> 06:45.280
and it's impossible to tell us
from the robbers,

06:46.680 --> 06:50.160
so any attempts of assault

06:51.600 --> 06:54.200
-could cost the lives...
-"The Dalí with the megaphone

06:54.280 --> 06:57.080
-is giving her orders.
-The one with the megaphone is a robber."

07:00.440 --> 07:01.960
"I request the green light, sir.

07:05.320 --> 07:06.480
Target in range.

07:07.280 --> 07:09.880
They're coming in, last chance, sir.

07:11.480 --> 07:12.640
Last chance, sir.

07:12.920 --> 07:14.920
They're coming in, I repeat,
they're coming in."

07:15.000 --> 07:16.200
No, don't shoot.

07:16.560 --> 07:19.880
Don't shoot, do you hear me? Let them in,

07:19.960 --> 07:23.280
let them go back in.
Do you hear me? Let them in.

07:25.800 --> 07:28.800
"As we have just seen,
the robbers have read a statement

07:28.880 --> 07:31.880
where they said they regret
having hurt the police officers."

07:31.960 --> 07:34.360
It seems the hostages
are in perfect health

07:34.440 --> 07:37.880
"and the assailants
do not intend to use violence."

07:58.720 --> 08:01.960
"My daughter, I know
you don't like Paula sleeping in your bed,

08:02.240 --> 08:04.640
but she insisted
and I didn't want to argue with her.

08:04.720 --> 08:05.880
Don't get angry."

08:37.360 --> 08:38.840
We're locked up

08:39.560 --> 08:42.640
and we really don't know
how long this could last,

08:42.720 --> 08:46.200
but as long as they don't blow
my head up, I'll take care of you.

08:46.280 --> 08:50.560
As long as you don't try to trick me,
or communicate with the outside,

08:51.360 --> 08:52.400
everything will be fine.

08:54.560 --> 08:56.640
From now on we're getting organized.

08:57.840 --> 09:02.040
We're giving you some tasks
so you don't feel down.

09:05.120 --> 09:07.240
-What's your name?
-Pablo.

09:07.920 --> 09:08.800
Do you do any exercise?

09:09.200 --> 09:11.560
Yes, I'm the athletic captain at school.

09:14.640 --> 09:16.480
Step forward, captain.

09:24.120 --> 09:25.000
Step forward.

09:28.200 --> 09:29.240
Man!

09:29.840 --> 09:30.800
Arturito.

09:32.080 --> 09:34.560
-Did you sleep well?
-Well, yes.

09:35.480 --> 09:38.560
Fine. Tell me, are you good at DIY?

09:38.720 --> 09:41.640
No, no, sir, I'm totally hopeless.

09:41.720 --> 09:44.600
In fact, when I have a flat tyre,
my wife changed it.

09:44.760 --> 09:46.920
Are you telling me you don't have a drill?

09:47.000 --> 09:48.480
-No.
-Think carefully what you say,

09:48.560 --> 09:50.880
because I have
a fucking lie detector right here.

09:57.760 --> 09:58.640
Yes.

10:01.720 --> 10:05.960
Let's see... Second chance.
Are you good at DIY?

10:07.320 --> 10:10.000
-I hold my own.
-Step forward.

10:18.040 --> 10:20.600
Would you feel better
if we brought you a tranquilizer?

10:20.720 --> 10:22.960
-Yes, please.
-Very well.

10:23.200 --> 10:26.680
-Does anyone else need medication?
-Me. I'm diabetic.

10:27.280 --> 10:30.320
-Come with Sonsoles, please.
-And me. I'm taking sertraline.

10:32.640 --> 10:33.560
Anyone else?

10:34.440 --> 10:35.320
Me.

10:37.960 --> 10:40.080
I'd like to ask for an abortion pill.

10:42.120 --> 10:44.160
You said you don't know
how many days we'll be here

10:44.320 --> 10:46.280
and I'd like to sort this out
as soon as possible.

10:46.360 --> 10:48.640
You'll get it today. You, come with me,

10:48.720 --> 10:51.760
I'm taking you to Mr Román's office,
you'll be more relaxed there.

10:51.920 --> 10:52.920
I also have a request.

10:55.520 --> 10:56.520
Yes?

10:57.720 --> 11:00.240
I'd like to erase a picture
from the internet.

11:00.400 --> 11:01.880
I'm sorry, that's not in my hands.

11:02.040 --> 11:04.400
I've been tricked,
they took me to a toilet

11:04.480 --> 11:06.120
and they got a picture of me naked.

11:07.360 --> 11:10.720
And now my parents, my teachers,
all the media are seeing it.

11:11.320 --> 11:14.880
You can record a message,
a video, so they calm down,

11:14.960 --> 11:16.280
and we'll send it.

11:20.360 --> 11:23.920
All of you will be allowed
to record messages for your families.

11:24.320 --> 11:26.440
Nairobi, come on.

11:30.200 --> 11:34.160
Come on, tough guys,
your hands behind your head

11:34.320 --> 11:36.680
and move to the left in a row,
sticking your chests out

11:36.760 --> 11:39.920
as if you were the national team.
Move, athlete.

11:40.400 --> 11:42.160
Do you see this dotted line?

11:43.040 --> 11:46.960
You're going to break the concrete
not going one centimetre away from it,

11:47.320 --> 11:50.840
as if it were a cut-out for children.

11:51.640 --> 11:54.440
There are 48 metres downward
until you get to the sewer pipe.

11:54.520 --> 11:58.320
The shift will last three hours.
And when you finish your shift

11:58.960 --> 12:01.360
and you go back with the hostages,
not a fucking word

12:01.440 --> 12:03.080
about what we're doing down here.

12:03.440 --> 12:05.360
-Any questions?
-No.

12:05.440 --> 12:07.720
That's good, that means I was clear.

12:08.440 --> 12:12.120
Come on, let's get to work.
You, put on the hearing protection

12:12.720 --> 12:15.160
-and take the hammer.
-I've never used one of those.

12:15.240 --> 12:16.840
There's a first time for everything.

12:27.160 --> 12:28.520
And be careful.

12:30.240 --> 12:32.600
You wouldn't be the first one
to lose a foot with that.

12:42.680 --> 12:46.360
-"Dad, mum, I'm fine."
-In Spanish, please.

12:48.960 --> 12:50.840
Hi, dad. Hi, mum.

12:51.560 --> 12:55.720
I'm fine, they feed us
and I've slept in a bag.

12:57.240 --> 13:00.280
Mum, this is not awful, okay?
There's no violence.

13:00.560 --> 13:02.000
"Mum", mum.

13:04.640 --> 13:07.040
I guess you've seen the photo
I uploaded on the internet.

13:07.320 --> 13:10.320
I didn't upload that photo and it doesn't
have to do with the kidnapping,

13:11.000 --> 13:13.600
it was a classmate who tricked me and...

13:18.880 --> 13:19.760
I can't.

13:19.840 --> 13:22.360
Do not give so much importance
to this photo. It's...

13:23.600 --> 13:26.080
It's just like when you go topless
on the beach, you know?

13:26.160 --> 13:27.040
Nobody cares.

13:28.920 --> 13:31.080
I don't go topless on the beach.

13:31.880 --> 13:34.320
And I don't kiss with boys
in the toilets of a museum.

13:35.480 --> 13:37.800
When my arm was put in a cast
it was the most exciting thing

13:37.880 --> 13:39.120
that happened to me this year.

13:40.560 --> 13:42.320
A kidnapping is more exciting.

13:49.960 --> 13:53.400
Well, think about
what you're telling your parents, okay?

13:54.080 --> 13:57.000
And calm down, I'll wait for you. Here.

14:05.800 --> 14:08.840
-You're serious. What's wrong?
-Why the fuck do you care?

14:09.280 --> 14:12.960
I'm just a child, the bedtime hobby
of the last five months, right?

14:16.400 --> 14:17.600
The silly guy with the badge.

14:18.920 --> 14:21.160
I said you were a child
and that I never would be with you

14:21.240 --> 14:23.320
so that you didn't get a bullet
in your breastbone,

14:23.520 --> 14:25.520
because I don't give a damn
if it's me who gets it.

14:25.600 --> 14:27.720
You don't believe that,
you didn't do it for me.

14:27.800 --> 14:29.400
What's the matter with you all?

14:29.880 --> 14:32.080
Since I came here
you're always making scenes.

14:34.280 --> 14:35.760
They've turned on a phone.

14:38.800 --> 14:40.200
It's Alison Parker's.

14:41.080 --> 14:42.000
Hack it.

14:43.440 --> 14:45.480
You know what's up?
I'm sure you waited for us

14:45.560 --> 14:49.320
to get out of Toledo to start with
all this fucking shit that I'm a child.

14:50.240 --> 14:51.880
She's trying to log in in her profile.

14:52.480 --> 14:53.800
Come on, come on.

14:55.240 --> 14:56.960
If I was your fucking gigolo,
just tell me.

15:01.280 --> 15:02.880
You were my fucking gigolo.

15:06.480 --> 15:07.560
You were everything.

15:08.360 --> 15:10.000
-I'm inside.
-Record it.

15:12.480 --> 15:14.360
I don't want to go on
with this conversation.

15:14.720 --> 15:16.920
You have the fucking nerve
to tell me you're mourning

15:17.000 --> 15:19.360
for your boyfriend, right?
You didn't seem to be mourning

15:19.440 --> 15:21.320
when you asked me
to push you against the wall.

15:22.040 --> 15:23.840
I didn't see the rosary
among your fingers.

15:24.880 --> 15:27.320
If you ever talk to me that way,
I'll smash your face.

15:28.960 --> 15:30.280
Change to selfie camera.

15:37.000 --> 15:40.200
Hey, what the fuck are you doing?
What the fuck are you doing?

15:40.280 --> 15:41.840
-No, no!
-Fucking hell, give me that!

15:41.920 --> 15:42.800
Hold on!

15:43.520 --> 15:44.480
It's offline.

15:47.280 --> 15:48.160
Rewind.

15:48.720 --> 15:50.480
Stop it. Double the pixels.

15:58.280 --> 15:59.240
We've got him.

16:15.200 --> 16:17.320
-They're going to kill us.
-But what are you saying?

16:17.400 --> 16:18.840
-They're going to kill us.
-Hush!

16:18.920 --> 16:22.160
And then they'll run away
using the tunnel we're making for them.

16:22.320 --> 16:25.600
-It'll be a slaughter.
-Shut up, you don't know anything.

16:27.880 --> 16:32.880
Think for a while, huh? Do you think they
are so stupid as to set us free

16:33.080 --> 16:37.400
so we can go to the police station
to identify them? Think, jeez.

16:38.280 --> 16:41.120
-We're fucked.
-Two times they've told me

16:41.200 --> 16:42.440
I'm a dead man.

16:46.560 --> 16:48.400
-Look what's under the canvas.
-Huh?

16:48.480 --> 16:50.880
Look what's under them.
I'm not staying here

16:50.960 --> 16:53.440
waiting like a guinea pig
on my knees to be killed

16:53.520 --> 16:55.720
without doing anything.
Look under the canvas,

16:55.800 --> 16:57.640
see if you find weapons at least, come on.

17:06.080 --> 17:06.960
Hello?

17:07.040 --> 17:10.960
"You call me at 6 in the morning
and leave a confusing message

17:11.040 --> 17:13.800
where you talk about being a figurehead,

17:13.880 --> 17:18.080
thugs and empty words.
Well, I'm not bearing that in mind."

17:18.360 --> 17:21.840
You resign and leave a robbery
with 67 hostages inside.

17:22.560 --> 17:24.800
"I'm phoning you

17:24.880 --> 17:27.400
so you can fucking tell me
that you won't be in charge of the case."

17:28.760 --> 17:30.040
I will be in charge of it.

17:31.360 --> 17:33.920
Raquel, there are things
which are above you.

17:34.720 --> 17:38.080
"National Security,
the Foreign Office, the CNI..."

17:38.440 --> 17:43.000
But, remember well,
you're the only person I know

17:43.720 --> 17:45.720
"who can solve this without violence."

17:48.520 --> 17:49.880
Thanks, superintendent.

17:50.200 --> 17:52.800
And now go back to that tent
and take the lead.

17:53.360 --> 17:55.080
We have the face of one of the robbers.

17:57.640 --> 18:00.400
-I'll cover you, come on.
-No way, no way.

18:00.480 --> 18:02.640
Put your gut into it.
What's the matter, captain?

18:02.720 --> 18:04.480
-No way, no way.
-Weren't you the captain

18:04.560 --> 18:06.160
-of the rugby team?
-Athletics.

18:06.240 --> 18:07.240
Hurry then.

18:21.200 --> 18:22.360
There are containers.

18:24.960 --> 18:26.600
-It's petrol.
-Jesus!

18:29.720 --> 18:32.520
-And ammunition.
-Holy shit!

18:36.480 --> 18:37.440
What's that?

18:40.240 --> 18:41.520
Are they drugs?

18:42.400 --> 18:44.560
This is heroin. It's heroin, man.

18:45.240 --> 18:49.000
Jeez, leave that right now,
it's the fucking plastic explosive.

18:49.080 --> 18:51.240
Leave it, come to dig, come to dig.

18:56.720 --> 18:58.840
Can anybody tell me why that machine

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
-isn't working?
-We're resting.

19:01.080 --> 19:04.400
You'll rest when I tell you.
Or when it's your turn.

19:04.760 --> 19:07.640
Okay, we'll go back to it right now.

19:31.920 --> 19:33.040
Inspector, please.

19:33.480 --> 19:36.840
Inspector, is there a conflict
between Intelligence and the Police?

19:36.920 --> 19:39.880
Were the negotiations cancelled
because of your family situation

19:39.960 --> 19:42.120
-after your complaint for ill-treatment?
-What?

19:42.200 --> 19:43.400
That's all, okay?

19:44.560 --> 19:46.800
-How does that scum know that?
-I don't know.

19:51.720 --> 19:53.000
You're already back?

20:02.080 --> 20:04.120
-Have you got a minute?
-Sure.

20:09.200 --> 20:10.600
Colonel Prieto.

20:12.320 --> 20:15.160
Look, I've been a bit nervous
these last hours,

20:15.240 --> 20:18.480
but I'd like our relationship
to be a little smoother.

20:18.880 --> 20:21.600
I think both of us
can contribute a lot in this crisis.

20:22.360 --> 20:26.080
I appreciate your "mea culpa."
So here I am,

20:26.160 --> 20:29.360
completely at your disposal.
But I want you to know,

20:29.760 --> 20:31.920
before there are any misunderstandings,

20:33.040 --> 20:34.600
that I'm a married man.

20:35.600 --> 20:37.880
Raquel, Raquel.

20:39.680 --> 20:43.000
A male, not older than 25, we recorded him
with Alison Parker's mobile phone.

20:43.160 --> 20:44.160
Identity?

20:44.520 --> 20:47.800
We're on it, facial recognition
are checking the PERPOL.

20:48.040 --> 20:51.360
-I want to see the whole video.
-Play the image.

20:56.760 --> 20:58.800
We couldn't record more than six seconds.

20:59.200 --> 21:00.120
Stop it there.

21:00.600 --> 21:01.840
It looks like a Makarov.

21:02.240 --> 21:05.360
No, it's a Strizh 9mm, it's also Russian.

21:05.960 --> 21:07.640
It's rare to see them here.

21:08.160 --> 21:10.320
Tell the judicial police to question

21:10.400 --> 21:13.400
all the informers from the East
in control of the black market.

21:13.760 --> 21:15.800
-What's that on the wall?
-Telephones.

21:16.800 --> 21:18.640
Play the images of the back camera.

21:22.480 --> 21:24.960
What do the labels say? Enlarge.

21:27.040 --> 21:27.920
The hostage list?

21:33.240 --> 21:34.360
They're their phones.

21:34.720 --> 21:36.680
Recognition can have his identity

21:36.840 --> 21:39.760
-in an hour or two.
-No, we're not waiting so long.

22:33.680 --> 22:36.120
Such a special connection.
Don't you find it striking?

22:36.480 --> 22:39.360
"I was just about to call you,
at this very moment."

22:40.360 --> 22:43.320
Well, considering I'm the negotiator
and you the robber...

22:43.480 --> 22:47.080
But we shouldn't allow this crime
interfere with our relationship.

22:47.240 --> 22:49.200
Don't know about you,
but I see this as a chance.

22:49.280 --> 22:51.680
-"A chance for what?"
-To get to know each other.

22:52.640 --> 22:54.640
"I assure you that if we had met in a bar,

22:54.720 --> 22:56.880
you wouldn't have paid
any attention to me.

22:57.240 --> 22:58.400
Tell me, inspector."

23:01.560 --> 23:03.360
Have you ever faked an orgasm?

23:08.160 --> 23:09.040
No.

23:09.600 --> 23:11.800
Please, inspector,
I beg you, don't lie to me.

23:12.080 --> 23:13.440
Think about it, please.

23:17.760 --> 23:20.000
Maybe yes, maybe I've done it.

